FT  28 NOV 92 / Letter: Ousted for the wrong reason
Sir, Gerald Ratner's institutional investors should have called for his
resignation because he had misread the market and was selling products in
his shops which did not meet his customers' aspirations for better quality
and design rather than causing his resignation because he spoke the truth.
It would seem that honesty is not always the best policy when dealing with
the City]
Terence Conran,
512 The Butlers Wharf
Building,
36 Shad Thames,
London SE1 2YE
